flowRoot.flowPara: World Population Day is an annual event observed on July 11 every year, which seeks to raise awareness of global population issues such as the importance of family planning, including gender equality, poverty, maternal health and human rights. The day is observed to build awareness of population issues and its impact on development and environment. The World Population Day is inspired by the public interest in Five Billion Day marked on July 11, 1987.
